## Hints for Future Agents
- SKILL.md is loaded ONCE at bot startup via /home/joshf/discord-ticket/src/index.ts:23 calling loadSkill(skillPath). Any edit requires a service restart (`sudo systemctl restart discord-ticket`) before it takes effect. Do NOT just edit the file and assume it's live.
- The bot is system-scope (/etc/systemd/system/discord-ticket.service), not user-scope. `systemctl --user status discord-ticket` returns "Unit could not be found" — that's expected, use plain `systemctl status discord-ticket`.
- Bot user is "House MD#3486" per discord-ready log line.
- The SKILL.md `interview_reply` audience is non-technical (player friends and family), so the bot must not leak label names like "agent-swarm" into outgoing Discord replies. The labels go on the GitHub issue body, not the chat.

## Codebase Discoveries
- /home/joshf/discord-ticket/.claude/skills/feature-request-interviewer/SKILL.md is the live skill file. The `.claude/skills/` directory in this repo is shipped as part of the bot install, not a Claude Code agent definition.
- Greenhouse spec format (from /home/joshf/code/greenhouse/src/dispatcher.ts:39-78): every dispatched run gets `## Labels` block listing all GitHub labels on the source issue. So leads can read `agent-swarm` straight from `.greenhouse/<seedsId>-spec.md` without needing extra plumbing.

